They are fully trained soldiers but after training are deployed as military police (policing the other 3 branches), as royal guards and close protection, as immigration in airports and on trains and roads - if you have entered Schiphol airport you'd have come across them  sitting in cabins checking passports, but most foreigners would just assume that they are police. When a grenade or something similar is found it's dealt with by EOD (explosieven opruimingsdienst) from the army, with normal police.
